The '''Abu Dhabi Cultural Foundation''' was founded in 1981 as a center of art and learning.  It is located in the middle of downtown [[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]], off [[Khalifa Street]] and next to the White Fort, also known as [[Qasr al-Hosn|Qasr al-Hosn Palace]].  The center hosts a variety of events, including art exhibits, lectures, concerts and movies, and arts workshop classes.  The foundation is operated under the [[Abu Dhabi Authority for Culture and Heritage]].<ref>{{ cite web|url=http://www.cultural.org.ae/E/CF.htm |title=Abu Dhabi Authority for Culture and Heritage |publisher=[[Abu Dhabi Authority for Culture and Heritage]] |accessdate=2007-12-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080328102921/http://www.cultural.org.ae/E/CF.htm |archivedate=2008-03-28 }}</ref>

