The '''European Tyre and Rim Technical Organisation''' (ETRTO) exists to specify and harmonise sizes of rims and their associated [[pneumatic tyre]]s across the [[European Union]]. ETRTO sizes apply to rims for vehicles of all types, including bicycles. The great advantage of ETRTO sizing is that it is unambiguous; previously, nominal dimensions were used which were interpreted in different ways by different countries and manufacturers - a problem for the end user.
ETRTO works in liaison with the [[International Organization for Standardization]] to develop relevant standards.<ref>[http://www.iso.org/iso/about/organizations_in_liaison/organizations_in_liaison_details.htm?id=9056&LiaisonList=True List of ISO committees in liaison with ETRTO]</ref>
