{{infobox WorldScouting | type = organization | image = Fédération Ivoirienne du Scoutisme Féminin.png | caption = Ivory Coast Federation of Female Scouting | name = Fédération Ivoirienne du Scoutisme Féminin | headquarters = | location = | country = Ivory Coast | f-date = 1937 | founder = | award-for = | members = 1,900 | chiefscouttitle = | chiefscout = | owner = | affiliation = [[World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts]] }}
The '''Fédération Ivoirienne du Scoutisme Féminin''' (''Ivory Coast Federation of Female Scouting'') is the national [[Girl Guides|Guiding]] organization of [[Côte d'Ivoire]]. It serves 1,900 members (as of 2008).<ref name="WAGGGS_membership">{{cite web|url=http://www.wagggsworldconference.org/en/grab/2398/1/33rdWorldConfernce-QuotaDoc11Agenda13-ENGLISHFinal.pdf |title=33rd World Conference Document No. 11 |publisher=[[World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts]] |accessdate=2008-10-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722042841/http://www.wagggsworldconference.org/en/grab/2398/1/33rdWorldConfernce-QuotaDoc11Agenda13-ENGLISHFinal.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-22 |df= }}</ref> Founded in 1937, the girls-only organization became a full member of the [[World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts]] in 1963.
Members of the federation are: * ''Guides catholiques de Cote d'Ivoire'' * ''Eclaireuses laïques de Cote d'Ivoire'' * ''Eclaireuses unionistes de Côte d'Ivoire''
