The '''Greens of Andorra''' ({{lang-ca|Verds d'Andorra}}, VA) is a [[green politics|green]] [[political party]] in [[Andorra]].

==History==
The party first contested national elections in 2005,<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen D]] & Stöver P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p162 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> when they ran in the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2005|parliamentary elections]]. They received 3.4% of the vote and failed to win a seat in the [[General Council (Andorra)|General Council]].<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p164</ref> In the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2009|2009 elections]] the party received 3.2% of the vote, failing to win a seat.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p2048</ref> The [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2011|2011 elections]] saw the party receive 3.4% of the vote, and again fail to win a seat.<ref>[http://www.eleccions.ad/EG_2011/index.htm 2011 elections] Government of Andorra</ref>

