{{Infobox prepared food | name = Torta Tre Monti | image = | caption = | alternate_name = | country = [[San Marino]] | region = | creator = | course = | type = [[Cake]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[Wafer]]s, [[chocolate]] or [[hazelnut]] creme, chocolate [[Fondant icing|fondant]] | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Torta Tre Monti''' (from {{lang-it|“three mountain cake”}}) is a traditional [[San Marino|Sammarinese]] cake made of layers of thin waffled wafers cemented together by [[chocolate]] or [[hazelnut]] creme. The final product is covered in chocolate [[Fondant icing|fondant]]. It is similar to other layered desserts common to [[San Marino]], this one being representative of the [[Three Towers of San Marino]].<ref name=ALG3>{{cite web|url=http://adribarrcrocetti.com/main/2011/04/12/torta-tre-monti/|title=Cake Review|accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref>
In San Marino, the ''torta'' has been commercially produced by La Serenissima since 1942. The bakery markets both a full-size cake and snack-size version, in addition to a variation that includes coffee.<ref name=PLG3>{{cite web|url=http://www.laserenissima.sm/eng/index.asp|title=Producer's website|accessdate=17 April 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140325233211/http://www.laserenissima.sm/eng/index.asp|archivedate=25 March 2014|df=}}</ref>
